h1. Ext.ux.Alert

p. A closable div alert for ExtJS 4.2 apps.

h2. Installation

p. Place the folder ux in your project.

h2. Usage

p. In your application file, please add:

bc.. Ext.Loader.setConfig({enabled: true});

Ext.require([
    'Ext.ux.Alert',
]);

p. 4 options to use

bc.. var msg = 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut';
	Ext.ux.Alert.success('Well done!', msg);
	Ext.ux.Alert.warning('Warning!', msg);
	Ext.ux.Alert.info('FYI!', msg);
	Ext.ux.Alert.error('Error!', msg);

p. Alternative: call method show passing the message type

bc.. Ext.ux.Alert.show('title', msg, 'success');    	

h2. Example

p. Open example.html to see how to use it.

h2. Authors

p. Based on Sencha ExtJS example (http://docs.sencha.com/extjs/4.2.2/#!/example/menu/menus.html) 
p. and https://github.com/fabiojpoli/Alert
p. enhancements and closable option added by Loiane Groner (March 2014)

